1. OVERVIEW
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Purpose: Personal GitHub profile portfolio repository for Alan Szmyt. It serves
as an automated, self-updating showcase of engineering skills, projects, and
GitHub activity.

What Exists: A GitHub profile README powered by auto-generated metrics SVGs,
activity-based updates, and 70+ themed profile summary cards. All content is
refreshed daily via scheduled GitHub Actions workflows. A professional resume
PDF is also hosted in the repository.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. PROJECT STRUCTURE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Key Directories:
  .github/workflows/     3 GitHub Actions workflow definitions (automation core)
  assets/emojis/         Custom emoji image assets
  branding/              Header banners, logo, badge templates
  docs/                  Empty placeholder (only .gitkeep present)
  metrics/               Auto-generated GitHub metrics SVG files (4 panels)
  profile-summary-card-output/  70+ themed profile card SVGs (auto-generated)
  .vscode/               VS Code workspace settings and extension recommendations

Notable Patterns:
  - Single-purpose profile repository, not a monorepo.
  - Automation-first: all meaningful content is machine-generated.
  - Generated artifacts are committed back to the repository on a daily schedule.
  - Private reusable action (szmyty/github-profile-summary-cards) is checked out
    at runtime and removed before pushing to keep the repo clean.

